sql:
SELECT event_type, timestamp
FROM container_events
WHERE event_type = 'restarted';

external_knowledge:
Docker Swarm is a container orchestration tool for managing and scaling containers; 
A high memory usage percentage may indicate a container is consuming more memory than expected, potentially impacting performance; 
Top 5 containers imply the ones with the highest memory usage percentages.

sql:
SELECT container_name, MAX(timestamp) AS latest_timestamp
FROM containers
GROUP BY container_name;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_active_containers
FROM containers
WHERE status = 'running';

SELECT timestamp, cpu_usage
FROM containers
ORDER BY timestamp DESC;

SELECT container_name
FROM containers
WHERE mem_percentage = (SELECT MAX(mem_percentage) FROM containers);

SELECT container_name, cpu_usage
FROM containers
WHERE cpu_usage > (SELECT AVG(cpu_usage) FROM containers);

SELECT COUNT(*) AS active_container_count
FROM containers
WHERE cluster_id = 'cluster123' AND status = 'running';
